.SS RESIZE_ROWS
.PP
.proto_resize_rows
.PP
Modify an existing table by adding or removing columns.
To achieve the new row size, and this function will remove columns
from or add empty columns to the end of each virtual row.
.PP
A row size of zero or less will not be honored.
.RS 4
.arg_handle
.TP
.I new_row_size
is the requested new row size
.TP
.B WARNING
Be aware that this function modifies the underlying array.
It may be best to avoid the single-step table creation when the
table may be resized.
Use the
.BR append_data " and " index_rows
after creating an empty table with
.BR declare .

